    public class AVLTree<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>

    Self-balancing binary search tree using the algorithm defined by Adelson-Velskii and Landis.

      • findReplacementNode

        private AVLTree.AVLNode<E> findReplacementNode(AVLTree.AVLNode<E> node)
        Function to find a replacement for a node that is being deleted from a binary search tree. If the node has a null child, then the replacement is the other child. If neither are null, then the replacement is the largest value less than the item being removed. node is not null a node is deleted from the tree
        Parameters:
        node - The node to be deleted or replaced
        Returns:
        null if both of node's children are null node.left if node.right is null node.right if node.left is null modified copy of node with its data field changed

      • findLargestChild

        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • incrementBalance

        private void incrementBalance(AVLTree.AVLNode<E> node)
        Method to increment the balance field and to reset the value of increase or decrease. The balance field was correct prior to an insertion or removal, and an item is either been added to the right or removed from the left. The balance is incremented and the increase and decrease flags are set to false if the overall height of this subtree has not changed.
        Parameters:
        node - The AVL node whose balance is to be incremented
